<h1>A quick guide to using the Behaviour Composer</h1>
<p><span style='color: red;'>*NEW*</span> You can now <a href='http://resources.modelling4all.org/guides/behaviour-composer-direct-to-netlogo-guide' target='_blank'>run your models directly in NetLogo</a> (and avoid the problems of Java applets).</p>

<p>A good beginning tutorial is this 
<a href="http://resources.modelling4all.org/guides/Predator-prey-guide">
step-by-step guide to building an ecosystem</a> of predators and prey. Also try 
guides <a href="http://resources.modelling4all.org/guides/Networks-and-vaccination-guide">modelling epidemics</a> and
<a href="http://resources.modelling4all.org/guides/Sugarscape-Guide">building Sugarscape models</a>.</p>
<p>To start click on the <b><a href="#_BehaviourComposer_">Composer</a></b> area. If you are new to the Behaviour Composer you may want to 
<a target="_blank" href="http://resources.modelling4all.org/presentations/video-tutorials">
watch these videos</a>.</p>
<p>The main operations of the Behaviour Composer 
are creating <i>prototypes</i> and adding <i>micro-behaviours</i> 
to prototypes. A prototype is an agent that represents one individual of a 
particular kind. Typically a micro-behaviour to make copies is added to a prototype. A model is a 
list of prototypes.</p>
<ul>
	<li><span style="color: #800000; font-weight:700">To view 
	video tutorials</span> 
click on <a target="_blank" href="http://resources.modelling4all.org/presentations/video-tutorials">tutorials</a>.</li>
	<li><span style="color: #800000; font-weight:700">To load sample models</span> 
	click on the sample models link on the Library in the <b><a href="#_BehaviourComposer_">Composer</a></b> area.</li>
	<li><b><font color="#800000">To browse for micro-behaviours</font>
	</b>click on links in the <b><a href="#_BehaviourComposer_">Composer</a></b> area.</li>
	<li><b><font color="#800000">To add a micro-behaviour to a 
prototype</font></b> click on the micro-behaviour button and then click on the 
	prototype or click on a prototype and click on the add micro-behaviour menu 
	item. </li>
	<li><b><font color="#800000">To display a menu of operations</font></b> 
click on a prototype or one of its micro-behaviours. Operations include 
renaming, inactivating (for easy later re-activation), and removal.</li>
	<li><b><font color="#800000">To undo or redo any change</font></b> 
in a model use the browser's back and forward buttons or use the <b>
	<a href="#_History_">History</a></b> area<i>.</i></li>
	<li><b><font color="#800000">To run your model 
</font></b> click on the <b>Send Model to NetLogo</b> or <b>Run</b> button of the 
	<b><a href="#_BehaviourComposer_">Composer</a></b><i>
	</i>area depending upon <a href='http://resources.modelling4all.org/guides/behaviour-composer-direct-to-netlogo-guide' target='_blank'>which version you are using</a>.</li>
	<li><b><font color="#800000">To build multiple models 
	</font></b>click on the 
	<b>New Model</b> button of the
	<b><a href="#_Models_">My Models</a></b> area. You can 
	select and name your models in this 
	area.</li>
	<li><b><font color="#800000">To continue where you left off</font></b> 
last time you visited the site save or bookmark the current URL before closing 
your browser. (If cookies are enabled and you use the same browser this isn't 
necessary.) There is no 
need to save since your model is continually saved on the server. </li>
	<li><b><font color="#800000">To share your model</font></b>
click on the <b>Share</b> button of the 
	<b><a href="#_BehaviourComposer_">Composer</a></b><i> </i>area and then 
	choose among the URLs of your model in the newly created <i><b>Share</b> 
	tab</i> 
	and add to a blog, wiki, discussion forum, chat, or email.</li>
<li><b><font color="#800000">To open (or re-open)</b> <a href="http://resources.modelling4all.org/libraries/basic-library">the default library of micro-behaviours</a></font>
click on the previous link.</li>
	<li><b><font color="#800000">To create a new micro-behaviour</font></b>
	visit the
	<a target="_blank" href="http://resources.modelling4all.org/documents/programming-guide">micro-behaviour programming guide</a>.</li>
	<li><b><font color="#800000">To find other models</font></b> 
	use a customised search query (not yet implemented).</li>
	<li><b><font color="#800000">To report errors or make 
suggestions</font></b> please 
	<a target="_blank" href="http://code.google.com/p/modelling4all/issues/list">visit the project's issue tracker</a>.</li>
	<li><b><font color="#800000">To ask questions</font></b>
	<a target="_blank" href="http://groups.google.com/group/modelling4all/about">visit the 
Modelling4All discussion forum</a>.</li>
	<li><font color="#800000"><b>For accessibility help</b></font>
	 read 
	<a target="_blank" href="http://resources.modelling4all.org/documents/Accessibility-Help">the accessibility help page</a>.</li>
	<li><font color="#800000"><b>To find out more about ownership, liability, and use 
	of this software</b></font>
	 read 
	<a target="_blank" href="../../../legal/index.html">the legal information page</a>.</li>
</ul>
<p>For more information visit the
<a target="_blank" href="http://modelling4all.org">Modelling4All Project home 
